[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:70[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:53[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Remote Code Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability has been detected in Apache Tika's RTF [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser. The fuzzer identified unrestricted class/object creation based on [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternally controlled data during the deserialization of embedded objects within [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTF files. This vulnerability is classified as a high-severity security issue that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould allow arbitrary code execution depending on the classes available on the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasspath.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue is a **Remote Code Execution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRCE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** vulnerability stemming from unsafe [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization practices. The security scanner specifically identifies [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"Unrestricted class/object creation based on externally controlled data"[0m[39m as the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause, which is a well-known attack vector in Java applications.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Technical Details[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability manifests during the parsing of RTF [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRich Text Format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m files when[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe parser encounters embedded objects. The stack trace reveals the following [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution flow:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The RTF parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m processes an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTF file through its `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mparseInline[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The `TextExtractor` component processes RTF groups and triggers [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1475[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The `RTFEmbObjHandler` handles completed embedded objects via [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m217[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. At this point, Java's standard `[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is invoked, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich deserializes data from the RTF file[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. During deserialization, a custom `[0m[1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method is called [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mjaz.Zer.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m377[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. The security hook detects the dangerous operation and reports the finding[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Deserialization Point**: The vulnerability occurs at [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m217[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where untrusted data from an RTF file is deserialized using [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Attack Surface**: RTF files can contain embedded objects, and the parser [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to deserialize these objects without proper validation or restrictions on [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich classes can be instantiated[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Detection Mechanism**: The fuzzer's security hook [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`jaz.Zer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m successfully [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetected the vulnerability during the deserialization process, indicating that the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode attempted to create objects from externally controlled data[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Impact Scope**: The vulnerability's impact depends on the classes available on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe application's classpath. With the right gadget chains present, an attacker [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould achieve arbitrary code execution[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo obtain a complete understanding of this vulnerability, the following components [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be thoroughly investigated:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **RTFEmbObjHandler Class**: Examine the `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand how it processes embedded objects, what data sources it trusts, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether any validation is performed before deserialization[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **TextExtractor Class**: Review the `[0m[1;35mprocessGroupEnd[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at line [0m[1;36m1475[0m[39m to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand how RTF group processing leads to object deserialization[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **RTF Parser Architecture**: Understand the overall flow of how RTF files are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsed and where embedded objects are extracted and processed[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Deserialization Mechanisms**: Identify all locations in the RTF parsing [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase where `[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or similar deserialization methods [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare used[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Input Validation**: Determine what validation, if any, is performed on [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded object data before deserialization[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Class Whitelisting**: Check whether there are any mechanisms to restrict which[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses can be deserialized during RTF processing[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Alternative Handlers**: Investigate if there are other handlers or components [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the RTF parser that might perform similar unsafe deserialization operations[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of Code Snippets[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Core Insights[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Vulnerability Location**: The RCE vulnerability is in [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m, where [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called directly on untrusted bytes from RTF [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles without any class filtering or validation.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Root Cause**: When RTF files contain the `\javaobjdata` control word, the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser collects hex-encoded serialized Java object bytes and deserializes them [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsafely, allowing arbitrary code execution through Java deserialization gadget [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchains.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Attack Flow**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TextExtractor encounters `\javaobjdata` control word [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1274[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Sets `groupState.javaobjdata = true` and calls [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35membObjHandler.startJavaObjData[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1275[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1276[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Collects hex bytes via `[0m[1;35mwriteHexChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m489[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When group ends, calls `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1475[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unsafe deserialization occurs at line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m: `new [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Critical Logic to Preserve**:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The OBJDATA handling path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m191[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m198[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m uses safe structured parsing via [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFObjDataParser`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The PICT handling path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m211[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m processes image data safely[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The embedded document extraction framework must continue to work[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests expect javaobjdata functionality but only with safe objects [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Alternative Safe Approach**: The `RTFObjDataParser` demonstrates safe [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructured parsing without deserialization. It reads binary structures [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield-by-field and handles specific class types explicitly.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Approach: Remove Unsafe Deserialization from JAVA_OBJDATA Path[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe optimal fix is to **completely disable the unsafe deserialization in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJAVA_OBJDATA handling path** while preserving the rest of the RTF parsing [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality. This follows the principle that untrusted data should never be [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialized without strict controls.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Implementation Steps[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Modify `[0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the unsafe `[0m[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the JAVA_OBJDATA branch with safe handling that:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Logs a warning about skipped deserialization[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Records metadata indicating javaobjdata was encountered but not deserialized[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Optionally extracts the raw bytes as binary data without deserialization[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Does NOT call `[0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with deserialized content[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Specific Code Changes in RTFEmbObjHandler.java**:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the `[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method around lines [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m224[0m[39m:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Replace the try-catch block that performs deserialization[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Add a log statement indicating that javaobjdata deserialization is disabled [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor security reasons[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Set metadata to indicate the presence of javaobjdata without deserializing[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Optionally: Save raw bytes as an attachment with a warning in metadata[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Call `[0m[1;35mreset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to clean up state without triggering extraction[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserve Existing Functionality**:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the OBJDATA path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m191[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m198[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unchanged - it uses safe [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFObjDataParser`[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the PICT path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m199[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m211[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unchanged - it handles image data safely[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep all state management in `TextExtractor` unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjavaobjdata detection,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate transitions[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the `[0m[1;35mstartJavaObjData[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mwriteHexChar[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods unchanged[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do NOT modify the `[0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method or embedded document framework[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Add Logging**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Import `org.slf4j.Logger` and `org.slf4j.LoggerFactory` at the top of [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRTFEmbObjHandler[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Create a static logger instance[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a warning log when javaobjdata is encountered and skipped[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Rationale[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why This Is Optimal**:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Security First**: Completely eliminates the RCE vulnerability by removing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsafe deserialization of untrusted data[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Minimal Impact**: Only affects the JAVA_OBJDATA path, which is rarely used in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimate RTF files[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No Breaking Changes**: The parser continues to handle all other RTF features [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mtext, images, OLE objects via OBJDATA[0m[1;39m)[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Follows Best Practices**: Aligns with OWASP guidance to never deserialize [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntrusted data[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Consistent with Tika's Design**: Uses the same pattern as OBJDATA [0m[1;39m([0m[39msafe [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructured parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vs. dangerous deserialization[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How It Preserves Existing Logic**:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. All RTF parsing continues to work [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgroups, control words, state management[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. OBJDATA embedded objects still work via safe RTFObjDataParser[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Picture/image extraction still works via PICT path[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The embedded document framework is unaffected[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Only the specific unsafe deserialization is removed[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why It Addresses the Issue**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The fuzzer detected RCE at line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m - this fix removes that exact call[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. No classes can be instantiated from RTF file data[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Gadget chain attacks become impossible[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The stack trace from `[0m[1;35mjaz.Zer.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will no longer occur[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation of Side Effects**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Test Breakage**: The test `[0m[1;35mtestJavaObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in RTFParserTest.java will need [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdating:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This test verifies javaobjdata deserialization with a String object[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update it to verify that javaobjdata is detected but not deserialized[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check that appropriate metadata is set indicating the presence of javaobjdata[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is acceptable since the test was testing dangerous functionality[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Legacy RTF Files**: Extremely rare RTF files with embedded Java objects:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Will have javaobjdata detected but not extracted[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Metadata will indicate the presence of javaobjdata[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users can be informed that deserialization was skipped for security[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is an acceptable trade-off for eliminating RCE[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No Broad Exception Catching**: The fix doesn't add try-catch blocks that hide [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors; it simply removes the dangerous code path[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Similar Solutions in Codebase**:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe RTFObjDataParser provides a model for safe handling:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It parses binary structures field-by-field[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It validates format IDs and structure before processing[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It handles specific class types explicitly without deserialization[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is the pattern that should be followed for all embedded object handling[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Alternative Considered and Rejected[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Creating a Whitelist-Based ObjectInputStream**: [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Could override `[0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to allow only safe classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39msimilar to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mForkObjectInputStream pattern at line [0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Rejected because:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Maintaining a safe whitelist is complex and error-prone[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Even [0m[32m"safe"[0m[39m classes can have unexpected behaviors[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - No legitimate use case justifies the risk[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The feature provides minimal value compared to security risk[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Removal is simpler and more secure than filtering[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue reports a Remote Code Execution [1m([0mRCE[1m)[0m vulnerability discovered    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         through fuzzing in Apache Tika's RTF parser. The vulnerability occurs during        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         deserialization of Java objects embedded in RTF files, specifically in the          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method at line [1;36m217[0m. The patch attempt    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         aims to disable Java object deserialization for security reasons by removing the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream` usage and replacing it with logging and metadata updates.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         However, the patch fails to compile due to a malformed class declaration that       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         causes the `LOG` variable to be unrecognized.                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Initial Issue                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer detected a `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh` exception indicating a Remote Code  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Execution vulnerability. The stack trace shows that the vulnerability is triggered  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         when:                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. The RTF parser processes an RTF file containing embedded Java object data        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. The `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method is called at line [1;36m217[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. An `[1;35mObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` call deserializes untrusted data from the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTF file                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. The deserialization hook `[1;35mreadObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is invoked on the deserialized object    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mshown in the stack trace as `[1;35mjaz.Zer.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The vulnerability follows the classic unsafe deserialization pattern where          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         externally controlled data [1m([0mthe RTF file content[1m)[0m can instantiate arbitrary classes [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         available on the classpath, potentially leading to remote code execution. This is a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         well-known and critical security issue in Java applications.                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Key observations:                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The vulnerability is in                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` at  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         line [1;36m217[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The vulnerable code path is triggered when processing `JAVA_OBJDATA` state in RTF [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         files                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The fuzzer successfully created a malicious input that exploits this              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         vulnerability                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - The deduplication token `aa5f725795b842b8` indicates this specific vulnerability  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         pattern                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Patch Attempt                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch attempts to address the RCE vulnerability by:                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. **Removing the dangerous import**: Removes `java.io.ObjectInputStream` import to [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         prevent its usage                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. **Adding logging infrastructure**: Adds SLF4J Logger imports and declares a      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         static logger                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. **Disabling deserialization**: Replaces the entire deserialization block with a  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         security-conscious approach that:                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Logs a warning message explaining why deserialization is skipped               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Sets generic metadata without deserializing the object                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Sets the embedded class to [32m"java.lang.Object"[0m instead of the actual class      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changes content type to [32m"application/octet-stream"[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Records an exception in metadata indicating deserialization was disabled       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch also appears to attempt adding a class declaration `class                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTFEmbObjHandler [1m{[0m` and constants like `EMPTY_STRING`, though these changes are not [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         properly integrated.                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ### Compilation Error                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The patch fails to compile with the error:                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cannot find symbol                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           symbol:   variable LOG                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           location: class org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         This error occurs at line [1;36m217[0m where `[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is called. The root cause is that  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the patch incorrectly modifies the class structure. Looking at the patch diff:      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ```java                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - * [1m<[0m[1;95mp[0m[39m/>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- * <p/>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+class RTFEmbObjHandler [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    private static final Logger LOG = [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFEmbObjHandler.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    private static final String EMPTY_STRING = [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * This [0m[1;39m([0m[39min combination with TextExtractor[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m expects basically a flat parse.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch incorrectly places a class declaration in the middle of a Javadoc comment[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock. The lines with `* <p/>` are part of the class-level Javadoc, and inserting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`class RTFEmbObjHandler [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` here creates malformed code. This results in:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The actual class declaration appearing later in the file becomes a nested or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplicate class[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The `LOG` field declared in this malformed location is not properly associated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the class[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. When the code at line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m tries to use `LOG`, it cannot find it in the proper [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscope[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo properly address this issue and create a working patch, the following areas [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be investigated:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Class Structure**: Review the complete structure of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Where the actual class declaration is located[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing Javadoc structure[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Proper placement for static field declarations[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Existing Logging**: Check if the class already has logging infrastructure or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif other classes in the same module use SLF4J[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **RTF Metadata Constants**: Examine `RTFMetadata` and `TikaCoreProperties` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses to understand:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Available metadata fields[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Proper usage of `CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether `EMBEDDED_EXCEPTION` is a valid metadata field[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **EMB_STATE Enum**: Investigate the `EMB_STATE` enum to understand:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All possible states[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `JAVA_OBJDATA` state is triggered[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether other states might have similar security concerns[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Alternative Handling**: Research how other parts of Tika handle embedded [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects to ensure consistency:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How other parsers handle potentially dangerous embedded content[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether there's a framework-wide approach to security[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Configuration options for enabling/disabling risky operations[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Test Coverage**: Identify existing tests for `RTFEmbObjHandler` to understand:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Expected behavior when processing JAVA_OBJDATA[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether tests expect successful deserialization[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Impact of disabling this feature on existing functionality[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Dependencies**: Check the module's `pom.xml` to confirm SLF4J is available as [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma dependency for logging[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m: * Contains a core set of basic Tika metadata properties, which all parsers[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m: * will attempt to supply [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere the file format permits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. These are all[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m: * defined in terms of other standard namespaces.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m: * Users of Tika who wish to have consistent metadata across file formats[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m: * can make use of these Properties, knowing that where present they will[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m: * have consistent semantic meaning between different file formats. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNo[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m: * matter if one file format calls it Title, another Long-Title and another[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m: * Long-Name, if they all mean the same thing as defined by[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link DublinCore#TITLE[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m then they will all be present as such[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: * For now, most of these properties are composite ones including the deprecated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * non-prefixed String properties from the Metadata class. In Tika [0m[1;36m2.0[0m[39m, most[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * of these will revert back to simple assignments.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: * @since Apache Tika [0m[1;36m1.2[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
